## Week 2 Monday — Registry Run key analysis

### HKLM Run key (system-wide, requires admin to write)
- SecurityHealth → %windir%\system32\SecurityHealthSystray.exe
- Verdict: Legitimate — Windows Security tray icon

### HKCU Run key (user-level, no admin required)  
- OneDrive → C:\Users\MrAbT\AppData\Local\Microsoft\OneDrive\OneDrive.exe /background
- Verdict: Legitimate — Microsoft OneDrive sync client

### Key finding
Clean baseline established. Two entries, both Microsoft, both
expected paths. Any additional entries pointing to AppData\Roaming,
Temp, or Public folders would be immediate red flags.
